Andrew Trimble on his new Ulster deal
Media playback is not supported on this deviceIreland winger Andrew Trimble explains why he is happy to sign a new contract with Ulster.The 28-year-old has played for the Irish province 155 times, scoring a record 50 tries.He has 49 Irish caps but did not feature in the recent Six Nations campaign.